# Windows PowerShell Script Collection

## Overview

This repository contains a collection of PowerShell scripts designed for various administrative and automation tasks in Windows environments. These scripts are intended to simplify and streamline your workflow, enhance productivity, and demonstrate the capabilities of PowerShell scripting.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Windows operating system
- PowerShell (version 5.0 or later recommended)

### Installation

To use these scripts:

1. Clone the repository or download the desired scripts.
2. Open PowerShell as an Administrator.
3. Navigate to the directory containing the scripts.
4. To execute a script, run `.\script-name.ps1` (replace `script-name.ps1` with the actual script file name).

## Usage

Each script in this collection serves a specific purpose.

Refer to the comments at the beginning of each script for more detailed usage instructions.

## Contributing

Contributions to this collection are welcome! If you have a useful PowerShell script or improvements to existing ones, please feel free to fork this repository, make your changes, and submit a pull request.

